B.Pm=A.a(s(["Name the three jewels","Explain why they work together","Apply the trio to a daily choice"]),t.s)
B.a9u=new A.d4("U01_L06","Three Jewels (Ratnatraya)",B.Pm,"Which set is called the Three Jewels?",u.d,"Wealth, health, fame","The Three Jewels are right view, right knowledge, and right conduct. They guide how to see, understand, and act.","Without all three, growth is uneven. Understanding needs action to become real.","Before a choice, check if it fits right view, right knowledge, and right conduct.","Right view is basic belief in non-violence and the soul. Right knowledge is accurate understanding. Right conduct is living those insights.","Use the three jewels as a quick compass for everyday decisions.","Which trio makes up the Three Jewels?",u.d,"Faith, luck, ritual","U01_L07")
B.P5=A.a(s(["List the five great vows","Know who takes the Mahavrata","Describe their purpose"]),t.s)
B.a9k=new A.d4("U01_L07","Five Great Vows (Mahavrata)",B.P5,"How many great vows are there?","Five","Three","Mahavrata are strict vows for monks and nuns: ahimsa, satya, asteya, brahmacharya, aparigraha.","They reduce harm and attachment at the deepest level.","Householders use the same values in lighter, realistic ways.","The five great vows are full commitments to non-violence, truth, non-stealing, celibacy, and non-attachment.","Even small choices can move toward these vows.","Which list matches the five great vows?","Ahimsa, satya, asteya, brahmacharya, aparigraha","Prayer, fasting, charity, pilgrimage, ritual","U01_L08")
B.Q6=A.a(s(["Define anuvrata","Know who practices them","Explain their daily value"]),t.s)
B.a9h=new A.d4("U01_L08","Anuvrata (Small Vows)",B.Q6,"Anuvrata are mainly for:","Householders","Only monks","Anuvrata are smaller vows for laypeople, adapting the same values to daily life.","They make spiritual practice practical in family and work life.","Set one clear boundary like mindful speech.","Anuvrata balance spiritual aims with real responsibilities.","Consistency matters more than intensity.","Anuvrata are:","Smaller vows for laypeople","Secret teachings for scholars","U01_L09")
B.P_=A.a(s(["Explain ahimsa at three levels","Recognize intention as part of action","Practice a simple pause"]),t.s)
B.a9p=new A.d4("U01_L09","Ahimsa in Thought, Speech, Action",B.P_,"Ahimsa includes:","Mind, speech, and body","Only actions","Non-violence starts in thoughts, shows in speech, and ends in actions.","Harm often begins in the mind before it appears outside.","Pause before reacting and soften inner language.","Jain ethics treats intention as part of the act.","Replace harsh judgment with curiosity.","Ahimsa applies to which levels?","Thought, speech, and action","Only physical action","U01_L10")
B.R8=A.a(s(["Define satya","Connect truth with non-violence","Apply kind speech"]),t.s)
B.a9s=new A.d4("U01_L10","Satya (Truthfulness)",B.R8,"Satya means:","Truthfulness with care","Brutal honesty","Satya is truthful speech that avoids harm.","Truth without kindness can still hurt; Jainism balances both.","Speak what is true, useful, and gentle.","Satya is aligned with ahimsa.","Choose timing and tone that reduce harm.","Satya is best described as:","Truth spoken without harm","Saying everything you think","U01_L11")
B.Qv=A.a(s(["Define asteya","Identify subtle forms of stealing","Practice respect for resources"]),t.s)
B.a9m=new A.d4("U01_L11","Asteya (Non-Stealing)",B.Qv,"Asteya encourages:","Not taking what is not given","Taking only small things","Asteya is non-stealing in actions and intentions.","It builds trust and reduces greed.","Respect time, credit, and resources.","Stealing includes subtle forms like plagiarism or wasting others time.","Ask permission and give credit.","Asteya means:","Non-stealing","Non-speaking","U01_L12")
B.QC=A.a(s(["Define brahmacharya","Explain householders practice","See how restraint protects clarity"]),t.s)
B.a9c=new A.d4("U01_L12","Brahmacharya (Self-Restraint)",B.QC,"Brahmacharya focuses on:","Self-control in desires","Ignoring relationships","Brahmacharya is channeling energy wisely, not impulsively.","It protects clarity and prevents attachment from driving choices.","Notice triggers and choose moderation.","For monks it is celibacy; for householders it is fidelity and restraint.","Respect boundaries in media and conversation.","For householders, brahmacharya is closest to:","Fidelity and restraint","Complete avoidance of all contact","U01_L13")
B.PP=A.a(s(["Define aparigraha","Explain attachment vs ownership","Try a simplicity practice"]),t.s)
B.a9t=new A.d4("U01_L13","Aparigraha (Non-Attachment)",B.PP,"Aparigraha is:","Non-attachment","Collecting more","Aparigraha means limiting possessions and clinging.","Less attachment reduces fear and jealousy.","Simplify one area and share what you do not use.","Possessions are tools, not identity.","Ask: do I own this, or does it own me?","Aparigraha teaches:","Non-attachment and simplicity","Luxury and display","U01_L14")
B.Qn=A.a(s(["Define anekantavada","Reduce dogmatism","Apply perspective-taking"]),t.s)
B.a9z=new A.d4("U01_L14","Anekantavada (Many-Sided Reality)",B.Qn,"Anekantavada teaches:","Many-sided reality","Only one view","Reality has many aspects; no single view captures all.","It reduces dogmatism and conflict.","Ask what might be true from another angle.","Truth is complex, so humility is required.","Listen to others to complete the picture.","Anekantavada is the doctrine of:","Many-sidedness","Single absolute view","U01_L15")
B.QT=A.a(s(["Define syadvada","Use context in statements","Avoid extremes"]),t.s)
B.a9l=new A.d4("U01_L15","Syadvada (Conditional Truth)",B.QT,"Syadvada is about:","Conditional statements","No truth at all",'Syadvada uses "in some ways" to express partial truth.',"It helps communicate without extremes.","Add context before making strong claims.","Statements are valid in certain conditions.",'Use "from this perspective" to be precise.',"Syadvada emphasizes:","Conditional truth","Random opinions","U01_L16")
B.Qf=A.a(s(["Define nayavada","Understand partial viewpoints","Combine perspectives for balance"]),t.s)
B.a9r=new A.d4("U01_L16","Nayavada (Viewpoints)",B.Qf,"Nayavada focuses on:","Viewpoints","Ignoring evidence","Nayavada is the study of viewpoints to understand reality.","It trains careful thinking and fairness.","Separate the part from the whole in arguments.","Each naya highlights one aspect, not the whole.","Combine viewpoints for fuller understanding.","Nayavada is best described as:","A method of viewpoints","A rule of silence","U01_L17")
B.Sf=A.a(s(["Define nav tattva","Recognize key categories","Use them as a learning map"]),t.s)
B.a9x=new A.d4("U01_L17","Nav Tattva (Nine Realities)",B.Sf,"Nav Tattva means:","Nine realities","Nine rituals","Nine realities explain how the soul binds and frees from karma.","They provide a map of spiritual progress.","Identify what increases bondage and what stops it.","Key categories include jiva, ajiva, asrava, bandha, samvara, nirjara, moksha, punya, papa.","Use them to review actions daily.","Nav Tattva refers to:","Nine fundamental realities","Nine temple festivals","U01_L18")
B.S5=A.a(s(["Know there are eight main karma types","Connect karma with experience","Identify clarity-blocking karma"]),t.s)
B.a9n=new A.d4("U01_L18","Eight Types of Karma",B.S5,"How many main karma types are taught?","Eight","Four","Jainism describes eight main karma types affecting knowledge, perception, energy, and more.","It shows why souls experience limits.","Notice how emotions cloud clarity.","Knowledge-obscuring and perception-obscuring karma are key categories.","Cultivate calm to reduce new binding.","Jainism describes how many main karma types?","Eight","Ten","U01_L19")
B.Sg=A.a(s(["Define leshya","Link emotions to inner color","Shift toward brighter states"]),t.s)
B.a9q=new A.d4("U01_L19","Leshya (Inner Colorations)",B.Sg,"Leshya refers to:","Colorations of the soul","Temple architecture","Leshya are inner colorations shaped by emotions and intentions.","They show the quality of your inner state.","Shift from harsh to gentle intentions.","Dark leshya come from anger and greed; bright leshya from compassion.","Choose thoughts that lighten your inner color.","Leshya describes:","Inner colorations from emotions","Outer clothing rules","U01_L20")
B.PZ=A.a(s(["Define samvara","Explain how karma inflow stops","Practice mindful restraint"]),t.s)
B.a9g=new A.d4("U01_L20","Samvara (Stoppage)",B.PZ,"Samvara means:","Stopping karma inflow","Increasing karma","Samvara is the stoppage of new karma through discipline.","Without stopping inflow, shedding is slower.","Use vows and mindfulness to reduce harmful actions.","Right conduct seals the leaks.","Track one habit that invites negativity.","Samvara is:","Stoppage of karma inflow","Collection of more karma","U01_L21")
B.QX=A.a(s(["Define nirjara","Know it removes existing karma","Connect it with tapas"]),t.s)
B.a9v=new A.d4("U01_L21","Nirjara (Shedding Karma)",B.QX,"Nirjara is:","Shedding karma","Binding karma","Nirjara is the removal of existing karma.","It clears the soul over time.","Practice forgiveness and austerity.","Shedding happens naturally and through tapas.","Choose voluntary discipline to speed up clarity.","Nirjara means:","Shedding existing karma","Hiding karma","U01_L22")
B.P6=A.a(s(["Define moksha","Explain freedom from rebirth","Link daily actions to liberation"]),t.s)
B.a9w=new A.d4("U01_L22","Moksha (Liberation)",B.P6,"Moksha is:","Liberation","Rebirth","Moksha is freedom from the cycle of birth and death.","It is the ultimate goal of Jain practice.","Align goals with inner freedom, not just external success.","Liberation comes when karma is fully shed.","Small steps of detachment point toward moksha.","Moksha refers to:","Liberation from rebirth","A holy pilgrimage site","U01_L23")
B.Ri=A.a(s(["Define gupti","Name the three controls","Practice mindful restraint"]),t.s)
B.a9A=new A.d4("U01_L23","Gupti (Three Controls)",B.Ri,"Gupti are:","Controls of mind, speech, body","Festival days","Gupti are the three controls that protect conduct.","They prevent impulsive harm.","Guard one channel for a day: mind, speech, or body.","Control is not suppression; it is conscious direction.","Slow down before acting.","Gupti refers to control of:","Mind, speech, and body","Weather and seasons","U01_L24")
B.Qc=A.a(s(["Define samiti","Know it reduces accidental harm","Apply mindfulness in routine"]),t.s)
B.a9f=new A.d4("U01_L24","Samiti (Careful Conduct)",B.Qc,"Samiti means:","Careful conduct","Ignoring details","Samiti are five careful practices to reduce harm.","Attention prevents accidental violence.","Walk, speak, and handle objects mindfully.","Examples include careful walking and careful speech.","Mindfulness turns routine into compassion.","Samiti refers to:","Careful conduct to avoid harm","Fast ritual chanting","U01_L25")
B.R4=A.a(s(["Define tapas","Differentiate external and internal tapas","Use discipline wisely"]),t.s)
B.a9o=new A.d4("U01_L25","Tapas (Austerity)",B.R4,"Tapas are:","Austerities and discipline","Luxury comforts","Tapas are disciplines that reduce attachment and ego.","They strengthen will and clarity.","Try a simple fast or reduced indulgence.","There are external and internal tapas.","Use discipline for insight, not pride.","Tapas means:","Austerity and disciplined practice","Entertainment and festivals","U01_L26")
B.PY=A.a(s(["Identify Paryushan as a Jain festival","Connect it with repentance","Practice forgiveness"]),t.s)
B.a9d=new A.d4("U01_L26","Paryushan (Renewal)",B.PY,"Paryushan is:","A period of reflection and restraint","A harvest festival","Paryushan is a Jain festival focused on repentance and renewal.","It refreshes vows and relationships.","Do pratikraman and ask forgiveness.",'Forgiveness is central: "Micchami Dukkadam".',"Clear old resentments.","Paryushan emphasizes:","Reflection, fasting, and forgiveness","Competitive sports","U01_L27")
B.Sp=A.a(s(["Define samayik","Connect it with calm awareness","Practice brief meditation"]),t.s)
B.a9i=new A.d4("U01_L27","Samayik (Equanimity)",B.Sp,"Samayik is:","A practice of equanimity","A business meeting","Samayik is meditative equanimity, staying balanced.","It trains the mind to stay calm amid change.","Sit quietly and observe thoughts without reacting.","Equanimity reduces new karma binding.","Consistency builds inner stability.","Samayik focuses on:","Equanimity and inner balance","Public debates","U01_L28")
B.QS=A.a(s(["Define pratikraman","See how it reduces ego","Make a simple review habit"]),t.s)
B.a9j=new A.d4("U01_L28","Pratikraman (Self-Review)",B.QS,"Pratikraman is:","Self-review and repentance","Celebrating victories","Pratikraman is a practice of reflecting and correcting mistakes.","It prevents repetition and softens ego.","Review the day and resolve to improve.","It includes confession, apology, and resolve.","Honest review reduces inner baggage.","Pratikraman is best described as:","Self-review with repentance","A travel ceremony","U01_L29")
B.S1=A.a(s(["Identify Jain cosmology as a worldview","Know the universe is eternal","Keep focus on ethics"]),t.s)
B.a9e=new A.d4("U01_L29","Jain Cosmology (Loka)",B.S1,"Jain cosmology describes:","The structure of the universe","Only one planet","Jain cosmology describes a universe with distinct realms and no creator god.","It frames spiritual progress in a vast context.","Focus on ethics rather than speculation.","The loka is finite in shape but eternal in existence.","Use cosmology as inspiration for humility.","Jain cosmology teaches that the universe is:","Eternal and structured in realms","Created once and then ended","U01_L30")
B.QO=A.a(s(["Name the five supreme beings","Know their role in the path","Connect them to the Navkar Mantra"]),t.s)
B.a9y=new A.d4("U01_L30","Pancha Parameshti",B.QO,"Pancha Parameshti refers to:","Five supreme beings","Five elements","The five supreme beings are Arihant, Siddha, Acharya, Upadhyaya, and Sadhu.","They represent stages and roles on the path.","Offer respect to the qualities they embody.","Navkar Mantra honors these five, not any one personality.","Use their qualities as personal ideals.","Pancha Parameshti are:","Arihant, Siddha, Acharya, Upadhyaya, Sadhu","Earth, water, fire, air, space","U01_MASTER_TEST")
